article.headline: Dayton 69, Holy Cross 53
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Norman Plummer scored 19 points to lead Dayton to a 69-53 win over Holy Cross Saturday night. The Crusaders (6-2) took a 29-27 halftime lead, but Dayton (6-1) started the second half on a 13-3 run. Plummer scored eight points during the run and the Flyers led by at least five the rest of the way. Dayton scored 38 points in the paint. The Flyers shot 59.5 percent for the game (25 of 42) and 60 percent in the second half. Holy Cross made just six of 22 shots in the second half. Charles Little scored 16 points for Dayton. Keith Simmons led Holy Cross with 15 points and Torey Thomas had 13.
